{# Shared base for practice documents.

These are administrative documents (Dichiarazione di conformità DM 37/08,
Comunicazione al Comune, …) — NOT marketing PDFs. Three constraints
shape every choice here:

  1. Officials (Comune, distributore, GSE) skim hundreds of these per
     week. Brand color is reduced to a thin top rule + the title; the
     body stays serif, black-on-white, A4 with 20 mm margins (standard
     for protocollo).
  2. Pages must be self-contained for stapling — page-break-inside
     avoidance on each section, page-numbered footer.
  3. WeasyPrint can't load remote fonts reliably; we stick to system
     fonts. DejaVu is shipped with the WeasyPrint Docker base image
     and used as the @page default.

Templates extend this and override two blocks:

  {% block document_title %}{% endblock %}  — used in <title> and the
                                              top-of-page banner.
  {% block document_body %}{% endblock %}   — the main content.

The header bar (installer name + logo + brand stripe) is fixed across
documents to give the customer a recognisable thread.
#}
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="it">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<title>{% block document_title %}Documento pratica{% endblock %} — {{ installatore.ragione_sociale }}</title>
<style>
  @page {
    size: A4;
    margin: 20mm 18mm 22mm 18mm;
    @bottom-right {
      content: "Pagina " counter(page) " di " counter(pages);
      font-family: 'DejaVu Serif', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: #555;
    }
    @bottom-left {
      /* Document identifier — handy when officials archive paper copies. */
      content: "{{ pratica.numero }}";
      font-family: 'DejaVu Serif', Georgia, serif;
      font-size: 9pt;
      color: #555;
    }
  }

  body {
    font-family: 'DejaVu Serif', Georgia, 'Times New Roman', serif;
    font-size: 10.5pt;
    line-height: 1.45;
    color: #1a1a1a;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Brand stripe: a single thin rule at the top of every page —
     enough for the customer to spot the installer at a glance,
     without making the doc look like marketing material. */
  .brand-stripe {
    height: 4px;
    background: {{ tenant.brand_color }};
    margin: -4mm -4mm 14px -4mm;
  }

  .doc-header {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: flex-start;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #cfcfcf;
    padding-bottom: 10px;
    margin-bottom: 18px;
  }
  .doc-header .installer-block {
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    line-height: 1.35;
    color: #333;
  }
  .doc-header .installer-block strong {
    color: {{ tenant.brand_color }};
    font-size: 11pt;
  }
  .doc-header img {
    max-height: 38px;
    max-width: 140px;
  }

  h1.doc-title {
    font-size: 15pt;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-align: center;
    margin: 18px 0 4px 0;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    color: #111;
  }
  p.doc-subtitle {
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 10pt;
    color: #555;
    margin: 0 0 22px 0;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 11.5pt;
    color: {{ tenant.brand_color }};
    margin: 18px 0 6px 0;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
    padding-bottom: 3px;
    page-break-after: avoid;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 10.5pt;
    margin: 12px 0 4px 0;
    page-break-after: avoid;
  }

  table.kv {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 6px 0 10px 0;
  }
  table.kv td {
    padding: 4px 8px 4px 0;
    vertical-align: top;
    font-size: 10pt;
  }
  table.kv td.label {
    width: 38%;
    color: #555;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  table.kv td.value {
    color: #111;
  }
  table.kv tr {
    page-break-inside: avoid;
  }

  table.components {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    margin: 8px 0 12px 0;
    font-size: 10pt;
  }
  table.components th {
    background: #f4f4f0;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 6px 8px;
    border-bottom: 1.5px solid #aaa;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.4px;
  }
  table.components td {
    padding: 6px 8px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #e8e8e8;
  }

  ul.norme {
    margin: 6px 0 0 18px;
    padding: 0;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    color: #333;
  }
  ul.norme li {
    margin-bottom: 3px;
  }

  /* Signature block — the document is legally binding only when this
     is visible. Used by every doc with one or two signatories. */
  .sign-block {
    margin-top: 28px;
    page-break-inside: avoid;
  }
  .sign-row {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-top: 36px;
  }
  .sign-cell {
    width: 48%;
    border-top: 1px solid #1a1a1a;
    padding-top: 4px;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .sign-cell .role {
    color: #555;
    font-size: 9pt;
  }

  .muted { color: #888; }
  .small { font-size: 9pt; }
  .center { text-align: center; }
  .right { text-align: right; }
  .em { font-style: italic; }

  .callout {
    border-left: 3px solid {{ tenant.brand_color }};
    background: #fafafa;
    padding: 8px 12px;
    margin: 10px 0;
    font-size: 9.5pt;
    color: #333;
  }

  .page-break { page-break-after: always; }
</style>
</head>
<body>

<div class="brand-stripe"></div>

<div class="doc-header">
  <div class="installer-block">
    <strong>{{ installatore.ragione_sociale }}</strong><br>
    {% if installatore.sede %}{{ installatore.sede }}<br>{% endif %}
    {% if installatore.piva %}P.IVA {{ installatore.piva }}{% endif %}
    {%- if installatore.codice_fiscale and installatore.codice_fiscale != installatore.piva %}
      &nbsp;·&nbsp;CF {{ installatore.codice_fiscale }}
    {%- endif %}<br>
    {% if installatore.cciaa %}CCIAA {{ installatore.cciaa }}<br>{% endif %}
    {% if installatore.telefono %}Tel. {{ installatore.telefono }}{% endif %}
    {% if installatore.email %}&nbsp;·&nbsp;{{ installatore.email }}{% endif %}
    {% if installatore.pec %}<br>PEC: {{ installatore.pec }}{% endif %}
  </div>
  {% if tenant.logo_url %}
    <img src="{{ tenant.logo_url }}" alt="">
  {% endif %}
</div>

{% block document_body %}{% endblock %}

</body>
</html>
